                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/647</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Shanklin</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General at Mexico City</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Written at Vera Cruz, Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt, today,
                    of the Department’s instruction of March 12, No. 710, the contents of which will
                    be transmitted by me to American citizens inquiring in regard to the payment of
                    their mining taxes.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Arnold Shanklin.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
